OL,3,CIn pictures: The North West celebrates
OL,4,CWorld Book Day
OL,6,FChildren across the North West have
OL,7,Fbeen dressing up as their favourite
OL,8,Ffictional characters on World Book Day.
OL,10,FOn the first Thursday in March, every
OL,11,Fchild in school is provided with a
OL,12,Fvoucher to be spent on books. They are
OL,13,Fencouraged to dress up as a character
OL,14,Ffrom a book they have read to
OL,15,Fcelebrate the day.
OL,17,FIt started in the U.K. in 1998 and is
OL,18,Fdesigned to encourage more young
OL,19,Fpeople to read.
